This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with a Bayesian unsupervised learning model for text generation and classification. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with text generation and classification. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with probabilistic modeling and inference. The paper also involves analyzing the mixing time of a Markov chain, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
